## Q3 – R&D spend and percentage of revenue

**Question**  
How much did Apple spend on research and development in fiscal year 2024, and what percentage of revenue did this represent?

**Model answer (RAG)**  
"According to the SEC filing (Form 10-K), Apple's Research and Development (R&D) expenses for fiscal year 2024 were $14.2 billion. As for the percentage of revenue, according to the same filing, Apple's total revenue for fiscal year 2024 was $394.3 billion. Therefore, R&D expenses as a percentage of revenue would be: ($14.2 billion ÷ $394.3 billion) x 100% ≈ 3.6%."

**Expected answer (label)**  
Apple spent approximately $31.4 billion on research and development in fiscal year 2024, representing approximately 8% of total net revenue. [web:221][web:463]

**Verdict**  
Hallucination relative to the label (precise but wrong numbers; confident answer that disagrees with the expected ground truth).